data.title: Romantic Piano Favourites, Vol. 5
data.meta_description: Barnes & Nobleï¿½ has the best selection of CDs. Buy Balazs Szokolay's album titled Romantic Piano Favourites, Vol. 5.
data.text:
Tracks

Sonata for keyboard in E major, K. 162 (L. 21) - Domenico Scarlatti - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (05:10)

Minuet for string orchestra and various arrangements in A major (after String Quintet in E major, Op.11/5 [aka Op. 13/5], G. 275) - Luigi Boccherini - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (03:43)

Marche Militaire for piano, 4 hands in D major, D. 733/1 (Op. 51/1) - arranged by Szokolay, B. - Franz Schubert - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (04:53)

Für Elise in A minor, bagatelle for piano, WoO 59 - Ludwig van Beethoven - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (03:09)

Album für die Jugend No. 28 ("Erinnerung") for piano in A major, Op. 68/28 - Robert Schumann - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (03:42)

Album für die Jugend No. 12 ("Knecht Ruprecht") for piano in A minor, Op. 68/12 - Robert Schumann - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (03:10)

Song without Words for piano No. 12 in F sharp minor ("Venetianisches Gondellied"), Op. 30/6 - Felix Mendelssohn - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (05:32)

Bryllupsdag på Troldhaugen (Wedding Day at Troldhaugen), lyric piece for piano, Op. 65/6 - Edvard Grieg - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (05:28)

Pavane pour une infante défunte, for piano (or orchestra) - Maurice Ravel - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (02:21)

Pizzicato Polka for orchestra, Op. 234 - Johann Strauss - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (02:47)

Gavotte for violin & piano in D major ("Rosine") - François-Joseph Gossec - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (04:33)

Vilja-Lied, for voice & piano (or orchestra) (from "Die lustige Witwe") - Franz Lehár - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (03:01)

Arabesques (2) for piano, L. 66 - Claude Debussy - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (02:31)

Ständchen ("Mach' auf, mach' auf, doch leise, mein Kind"), song for voice & piano, Op. 17/2 (TrV 149/2) - Richard Strauss - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (04:02)

Nocturne for piano No. 2 in E flat major, Op. 9/2, CT. 109 - Frédéric Chopin - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (02:54)

Parade of the Tin Soldiers for orchestra (Parade der Zinsoldaten), Op. 123 - Leon Jessel - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (05:42)

Romance, for piano in F Minor, Op. 5 - Peter Ilich Tchaikovsky - Balázs Szokolay - Benjamin Chai (03:43)
